## NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES — ENFORCE IN EVERY RESPONSE

1. F3 CATALYST ORDER (NEVER change this):
   base → modifiers → decay → dhatu×freshness → escape → compare

2. F6 SIZING CHAIN (ALL 8 steps, IN ORDER):
   Kelly → cap 4% → cash account ×0.80 → gap risk →
   chaos time → fat tail → session/force → final shares

3. F17: belief = min(0.90, bayesian_posterior)  # HARD CAP

4. F18: dhatu_modifier = base_modifier × freshness_score

5. FTMO LIMITS (hard-coded, never from config):
   daily_limit = 0.04      # NOT 0.05
   drawdown_limit = 0.08   # NOT 0.10
   max_trades = 2          # Per day
   best_day_rule: today ≤ (2/3) × sum(other_profitable_days)

6. M-04 GATE: ConditionalExpectancyMatrix INACTIVE until n≥200 trades
   Agent D CANNOT make adaptations on INSUFFICIENT or PRELIMINARY data

7. Belief EXIT threshold = 0.35 (never override)
8. 20% cash reserve = enforced (never override)
9. TRADING_MODE=paper enforced until all validations pass

## CURSOR AGENT MODE PROMPTS

### When fixing Agent B (Dhatu):
"Acting as Agent B. Read src/agent_b.py and the Dhatu sections of
EVERYTHING_FINAL.md. [describe the issue]. Maintain F3 order exactly.
Reference principle numbers in comments. Use claude-opus-4-6."

### When fixing Agent C (Risk):
"Acting as Agent C. Read src/agent_c_ibkr.py or src/agent_c_mt5.py.
[describe the issue]. All 8 F6 steps must remain in order.
FTMO limits: 4%/8%/2trades. Use gpt-5.4."

### When adding a new pattern:
"Acting as Agent A. Add [pattern name] to src/agent_a.py.
Follow the PatternResult dataclass structure. Include:
chaos decay lambda, volume threshold check, entropy modifier.
FTMO budget check before returning result. Use claude-sonnet-4-6."

